],["$","path",null,{"d":"M5 12h14"}]]}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed","children":"Yes, but as a tiebreaker rather than a primary signal. CWV is part of Google's Page Experience signal. In competitive UK niches we see clear ranking lift when sites move from 'Needs Improvement' to 'Good', particularly on mobile."}]]}],["$","details","2",{"className":"group py-5","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 list-none","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-ink-50","children":"How do I measure INP accurately?"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"className":"grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full border border-ink-700 text-ink-300 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45","children":["$","svg",null,{"width":"12","height":"12","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"2.5","strokeLinecap":"round","children":[["$","path",null,{"d":"M12 5v14"}],["$","path",null,{"d":"M5 12h14"}]]}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed","children":"INP requires real-user monitoring — lab tools like Lighthouse can only estimate it. Use the web-vitals JavaScript library to report INP to your analytics, or pull from the Chrome User Experience Report (CrUX) BigQuery export."}]]}]]}]]}]
